In a parallel universe, there are not just two charges like positive and negative, but there are 26 
charges represented by lower english alphabets.
Charges have a property of killing each other or in other words neutralizing each other if they are of same charge and next to each other.

You are given a string S where each S[i] represents a charge, where 0 <= i <= |s| - 1.

You need to output size of final string followed by string after which no neutralizing is possible.

Sample Input;

12
aaacccbbcccd


SAMPLE OUTPUT

2
ad
